    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>IRON ORE TAKEOVER FIGHT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Alan Cowell</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Cowell, Alan</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Australia's Rio Tinto PLC makes $1.7 billion hostile takeover offer for rival North Ltd; investors in North expect other bids from Rio Tinto competitors (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Opening a possible bidding war, Rio Tinto P.L.C., one of the world's leading iron ore producers, made a $1.67 billion hostile offer for North Ltd., an Australian rival in which it already holds a 14.5 percent stake. Rio Tinto offered 3.80 Australian dollars, or $2.26, a share in cash, but North's stock shot up 33 percent, to 3.92 Australian dollars, indicating that investors are anticipating further bids from companies like Anglo American P.L.C., Billiton P.L.C. or WMC Ltd. North called the Rio Tinto offer inadequate.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
      </block>
